##HOW TO FIND SUITABLE CAMPAIGN 
Once you have joined the Whop server or Discord Server, go to the Active Campaigns section and evaluate each campaign carefully based on the following factors:

Platfrom - 
Before selecting a campaign, check which platform it supports. Most campaigns allow platforms like Instagram, TikTok, and YouTube. In rare cases, some campaigns may also include Facebook or X.
For beginners, it is better to focus on one platform only, preferably Instagram. Managing multiple platforms can become difficult and reduce consistency. Also, many TikTok campaigns are based on trending music and tend to end quickly, making them less stable. In comparison, Instagram campaigns are more consistent and beginner-friendly.
Although the process is similar across all platforms, this guide mainly focuses on Instagram, as it is the most reliable starting point and Instagram has more ways to make money than clipping like doing sponsorship and digital guide selling ( discussed in other folder in detail ) .
If the campaign doesn't allow the plaftrom you work on just simply move on with other campaign that allows you don't have evaluate the rest of the factors . 
Only check other factor if the campaign allows the platfrom you work on. 

RPM (Revenue Per 1000 Views) - 
RPM is one of the most important factors when choosing a campaign. It determines how much you earn per 1,000 views.
An RPM between $0.5 to $1 is generally considered good for beginners. Higher RPM campaigns are better, but they may also have higher competition or stricter requirements.

Three keys - 
Timeline : 
The campaign timeline refers to how long the campaign will remain active. This is especially important for new pages.
If you already have an old or active page that consistently gets views, you don’t need to worry much about the timeline. You can join most campaigns without concern because your content can start performing immediately.
However, if you are using a new page, the timeline becomes critical. New pages usually take around 7–10 days to gain traction and start getting good reach. If a campaign ends before that, you may not get any meaningful results or earnings.
A good timeline is anywhere between 2 weeks to a momth. You can ask the support team about timeline or just estimate on your own based of other two factors. 

Budget Strategy : 
The campaign budget determines how long the campaign can sustain payouts, so it is important to analyze it before joining.
First, check how much of the campaign budget is remaining. If less than 60% of the budget is left, it is generally not a good idea to join, especially for new pages.
Second, observe how quickly the budget is being consumed. If the budget is decreasing rapidly, it means many participants are active, and the campaign may end soon. Thus the campaign have lower timeline as budget gets over quickly.
For new pages, this is risky because the campaign might run out of budget before your content starts getting views. Therefore, always choose campaigns with sufficient remaining budget and slower consumption rate.

Competition : 
For Whop , If a campaign is run only on Whop, the number of participants is usually not visible. In such cases, you should rely on budget strategy (how fast the budget is being consumed) or directly ask the support team for insights.

For Discord , there are three cases 
    Case 1: Discord Server Running Campaign via Whop
If the Discord server redirects you to Whop for campaigns, then participant data will not be visible. In this situation, follow the Whop strategy:
Analyze budget consumption speed
Or ask support for clarity

    Case 2: Discord Server with Its Own Website
Some servers run campaigns on their own websites instead of Whop, but they still do not show participant numbers. In this case as well, follow the same approach:
Use budget strategy
Or contact support

    Case 3: Separate Discord Server for Campaign
In some cases, campaigns create a dedicated Discord server for participants. This is the best scenario to estimate competition.
You can check the number of members in that server to get an idea of competition.
👉 Example:
If the server has around 400 members, typically about 1% (≈ 40 people) are actively posting.
This level of competition is generally good for beginners.
However, if the number of active participants is too high, the campaign budget will get consumed quickly, reducing your chances of earning—especially if you are using a new page.

